{"submission_id":"sub_36c24d3340601fef","run_id":"2026-06-21T16-32-06-441Z_2895026-84e9bc05_ingest_meeting-doc-154966","submitted_at":"2026-06-21T16:38:35.591Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:36c24d3340601fefbddfec4742b51947c775a58360253f95291d1e26e9124f83","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_154966","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting154966_fare_evasion_rise","label":"Fare evasion on the rise, Eagle Team efforts","raw_text":"Interim President Crichlow commented that fare evasion is on the rise and discussed efforts to improve bus fare compliance, including through deployment of a revamped Eagle Team. ... He noted that the improved visibility of fare inspectors has resulted in an increase in paid ridership at intervention stops.","payload":{"claim_text":"Fare evasion is on the rise. Efforts to improve bus fare compliance include deployment of a revamped Eagle Team and new digital messaging conveying the importance of paying the bus fare. Improved visibility of fare inspectors has resulted in an increase in paid ridership at intervention stops.","subject":"bus fare compliance","data_type":"narrative","data_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"narrative","normalized_value":"narrative"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_154966","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_154966#p003_c0005","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_154966/blocks.jsonl","page_number":3,"block_id":"p003_c0005","text_sha256":"sha256:76833caeea86dff8d988dec5ebc5b509fff369638db8f8edef69b38162b67e12","text_source":"raw_text","role":"claim"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_86923cf60457bdaf","run_id":"2026-06-21T16-32-06-441Z_2895026-84e9bc05_ingest_meeting-doc-154966","submitted_at":"2026-06-21T16:38:48.245Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:86923cf60457bdaf2f7f5f485890e217ccbdc53faa5a0816665beb23a81d87a2","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_154966","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting154966_capital_plan_presented","label":"MTA 2025-2029 Capital Plan presented","raw_text":"Jamie Torres-Springer, President, MTA C&D introduced Deputy Chief Development Officer Tim Mulligan who, along with his team, developed the MTA's 2025-2029 Capital Plan. He explained that the capital plan is a comprehensive investment plan to keep the MTA transportation system running, to provide frequent and reliable service and improve customer experience, and to take action on climate change.","payload":{"claim_text":"The MTA 2025-2029 Capital Plan is a comprehensive investment plan to keep the MTA transportation system running, to provide frequent and reliable service and improve customer experience, and to take action on climate change. The capital plan would include upgrades to older subway cars, subway signals, substations, and structures to increase reliability and improve customer experience by ensuring accessible, safe, and comfortable stations. It would support NYCT's efforts to combat the effects of climate change, reduce emissions, and improve air quality.","subject":"MTA 2025-2029 Capital Plan","data_type":"narrative","data_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"narrative","normalized_value":"narrative"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_154966","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_154966#p003_c0013","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_154966/blocks.jsonl","page_number":3,"block_id":"p003_c0013","text_sha256":"sha256:b0aec4d162ae3ff5c940b2ca6a05a453ce2e52eedf1f237900120c9ef2b9a115","text_source":"raw_text","role":"claim"},{"source_id":"meeting_doc_154966","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_154966#p004_c